---
const marks = [
	{ top: "8%", left: "6%", size: "3.5rem", rotate: "-12deg", opacity: 0.3 },
	{ top: "72%", left: "10%", size: "2.5rem", rotate: "10deg", opacity: 0.25 },
	{ top: "16%", left: "90%", size: "3rem", rotate: "14deg", opacity: 0.3 },
	{ top: "78%", left: "86%", size: "4.5rem", rotate: "-8deg", opacity: 0.35 },
];
---

<section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#fbd9e9] py-28 lg:py-36">
	<div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true">
		{
			marks.map((m) => (
				<img
					src="/Question Mark.png"
					alt=""
					class="absolute"
					style={{
						top: m.top,
						left: m.left,
						height: m.size,
						width: m.size,
						opacity: m.opacity,
						transform: `rotate(${m.rotate})`,
					}}
				/>
			))
		}
	</div>

	<div class="container-page relative">
		<div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col text-center lg:block">
			<div class="order-1 mx-auto flex max-w-5xl flex-col items-center gap-2 lg:flex-row lg:flex-nowrap lg:items-end lg:justify-center lg:gap-1">
				<p class="text-balance font-display text-4xl whitespace-nowrap text-black sm:text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-semibold">
					How do you come in
				</p>
				<span class="flex shrink-0 items-end gap-1 lg:pb-1">
					<img
						src="/Question Mark.png"
						alt=""
						aria-hidden="true"
						class="h-8 w-8 rotate-[-8deg] sm:h-7 sm:w-7 sm:-translate-y-2 lg:h-11 lg:w-11"
					/>
					<img
						src="/Question Mark.png"
						alt=""
						aria-hidden="true"
						class="h-10 w-10 sm:h-9 sm:w-9 sm:-translate-y-4 lg:h-14 lg:w-14"
					/>
					<img
						src="/Question Mark.png"
						alt=""
						aria-hidden="true"
						class="h-8 w-8 rotate-[8deg] sm:h-7 sm:w-7 lg:h-11 lg:w-11"
					/>
				</span>
			</div>

			<p class="order-2 mx-auto mt-10 max-w-5xl text-left font-sans text-base leading-snug font-semibold text-black lg:order-none lg:text-2xl">
				Unlike low-ticket offers (like a chocolate bar, a piece of clothing, or anything below 500
				bucks) where people can just buy it and go about their day, high-ticket buyers need a
				genuine consultation with a real human.
			</p>

			<img
				src="/jackson.png"
				alt=""
				aria-hidden="true"
				class="order-3 mx-auto mt-8 w-96 rounded-2xl shadow-xl lg:order-none lg:mt-8 lg:w-136"
			/>

			<p class="order-4 mx-auto mt-4 max-w-5xl text-left font-sans text-base leading-snug font-semibold text-black lg:order-none lg:mt-6 lg:text-2xl">
				Before they make the decision to spend $2,000–$10,000 on a certain product or service.
			</p>

			<p class="order-5 mx-auto mt-6 max-w-5xl text-center font-sans text-xl leading-snug font-bold text-black lg:order-none lg:text-3xl">
				And a high-ticket closer must be skilled enough to:
			</p>

			<ul class="order-6 mx-auto mt-6 flex max-w-5xl flex-col items-center gap-3 lg:order-none">
				{
					[
						"Handle objections before they even show up",
						"Connect all the dots between the benefits and the stakeholder's problem",
						"Speak a CFO's language and understand ROI",
					].map((skill) => (
						<li class="flex items-center gap-4 text-left font-sans text-base leading-snug font-semibold text-black lg:text-2xl">
							<svg
								viewBox="0 0 24 24"
								class="h-8 w-8 shrink-0 -rotate-3 fill-none stroke-[#ff0894] stroke-[2.5] lg:h-10 lg:w-10"
							>
								<path
									d="M3.5 11.8c1.8 1.4 3.6 3.4 5 5.4 3-5.2 6.7-9.8 11.5-13.4"
									stroke-linecap="round"
									stroke-linejoin="round"
								/>
							</svg>
							{skill}
						</li>
					))
				}
			</ul>

			<p class="order-7 mt-12 text-balance font-script text-4xl font-bold text-violet-ray lg:order-none lg:text-5xl">
				Sounds confusing, right? Well, worry not!
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
